# Form Fields

**Canonical reference:** `src/features/incoming/forms/create-incoming-form.tsx`

All forms, dialogs, and sheets must match this field UI — subtle default sizing, shared Field primitives, consistent spacing.

---

## Components

Use shadcn Field primitives — not raw `<label>` + unstyled inputs:

| Primitive | Use for |
|-----------|---------|
| `FieldSet` + `FieldLegend` + `FieldDescription` | Form sections |
| `FieldGroup` | Vertical spacing / grids |
| `Field` + `FieldLabel` + `FieldError` | Each control |
| `FieldSeparator` | Between major sections |

Import from `@/components/ui/field`.

---

## Input sizing — use defaults, do not override

Use `Input`, `Textarea`, `DatePickerInput`, and `SearchableOptionCombobox` **without** height or font-size class overrides.

```tsx
// ✅ GOOD — default Input (h-9, text-base on mobile, md:text-sm)
<Input id={field.name} placeholder="e.g. 1024 (optional)" aria-invalid={isInvalid} />

// ✅ GOOD — numeric: only tabular-nums, no text-base
<Input {...numericInputProps} className="tabular-nums" />

// ✅ GOOD — textarea: min-height only
<Textarea className="min-h-[120px] resize-y" />

// ❌ BAD — oversized, inconsistent
<Input className="h-11 text-base" />
<Textarea className="min-h-[96px] resize-y text-base" />
```

`Input` / `Textarea` already use `text-base` on mobile and `md:text-sm` on desktop (iOS zoom-safe). Never add `h-11`, `size-11`, or redundant `text-base` on fields.

---

## Layout

**Full-page / card forms:**

```tsx
<FieldGroup className="@container/field-group gap-6">
  <FieldSet>
    <FieldLegend className="font-heading text-base font-semibold">Section title</FieldLegend>
    <FieldDescription>Section hint.</FieldDescription>
    <FieldGroup className="mt-4 grid grid-cols-1 gap-4 @md/field-group:grid-cols-2">
      <Field>…</Field>
    </FieldGroup>
  </FieldSet>
  <FieldSeparator />
</FieldGroup>
```

**Dialogs / compact forms:** `FieldGroup className="gap-4"` (single column unless a grid is needed).

Span full width in 2-col grids: `className="@md/field-group:col-span-2"` on `Field`.

---

## Validation

```tsx
function isFieldInvalid(meta: { isTouched: boolean; isValid: boolean }) {
  return meta.isTouched && !meta.isValid
}

<Field data-invalid={isInvalid}>
  <FieldLabel htmlFor={id}>Label</FieldLabel>
  <Input … aria-invalid={isInvalid} />
  {isInvalid && <FieldError errors={field.state.meta.errors} />}
</Field>
```

---

## Numeric fields

Import from `@/lib/form-utils` — do not duplicate locally:

- `numericInputProps` — spread on number inputs
- `parseOptionalNumber` — optional number onChange parsing
- Add `className="tabular-nums"` only (never `text-base`)

Use `inputMode="numeric"` / `type="tel"` for mobile numbers where appropriate.

---

## Combobox + inline action row

```tsx
<div className="flex gap-2">
  <div className="min-w-0 flex-1">
    <SearchableOptionCombobox … />
  </div>
  <Button
    type="button"
    variant="secondary"
    className="h-auto min-h-9 shrink-0 gap-1.5 px-3"
    aria-label="Add farmer"
  >
    <UserPlus className="size-4 shrink-0" />
    <span className="hidden sm:inline">Add Farmer</span>
  </Button>
</div>
```

---

## Footer / dialog actions

Use default `Button` sizes (`default` / `sm`). Do not force `h-11` on Cancel, Save, or submit buttons.

---

## Checklist

- [ ] No `h-11` / `text-base` overrides on `Input` or `Textarea`
- [ ] `FieldLabel` + `FieldError` + `data-invalid` / `aria-invalid` wired
- [ ] Section legends use `font-heading text-base font-semibold`
- [ ] Field grid uses `gap-4`; dialog forms use `FieldGroup gap-4`
- [ ] Numeric helpers from `@/lib/form-utils`
